text.section:
Any resolution or resolutions authorizing any bonds pursuant to this section may contain provisions, which shall be a part of the contract with the holders of the bonds, concerning
A pledge of or a security interest in the revenue derived from the construction subdistrict;
The amounts to be raised in each year by rates, rentals, and charges, and their use and disposition;
The setting aside of reserves or sinking funds and their regulation and disposition;
Limitations on the right of the district to restrict and regulate the use of the subdistrict facilities;
Limitations on the purposes to which the proceeds of sale of any issue of bonds to be issued with respect to the same construction subdistrict may be applied;
Limitations on the issuance of additional bonds for the same construction subdistrict; and
The procedure, if any, by which the term of any contract with bondholders may be amended or be abrogated, the amount of the bonds the holders of which must give consent, and the manner in which the consent may be given.
